What are popular DevOps tools?

Version Control: Git, GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket

CI/CD: Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI

Configuration Management: Ansible, Chef, Puppet

Containerization: Docker

Orchestration: Kubernetes

Monitoring: Nagios, Prometheus, Grafana

Cloud Platforms: AWS, Azure, GCP



---

5. What is Continuous Integration (CI)?
➡️ CI is the process of automatically building and testing code every time a developer commits changes to version control.
Example tool: Jenkins, GitHub Actions

Benefits:

Early bug detection

Consistent code integration

Fast feedback



---

6. What is Continuous Deployment (CD)?
➡️ CD automatically deploys code to production after passing all tests.
Tools: Jenkins, Spinnaker, ArgoCD

Goal: Deliver updates faster and with fewer errors.


---

7. What is Infrastructure as Code (IaC)?
➡️ IaC means managing infrastructure (servers, networks, storage) using code instead of manual configuration.
Example tools: Terraform, CloudFormation, Ansible

Benefit:

Version control for infrastructure

Consistency and automation



---

8. What is the difference between Ansible, Puppet, and Chef?

Tool	Language	Type	Agent/Agentless

Ansible	YAML	Push-based	Agentless
Puppet	DSL (Ruby)	Pull-based	Agent required
Chef	Ruby	Pull-based	Agent required



